    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1055"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1055">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/711</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McAdoo</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department</hi>, <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-27">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For your consideration in connection with this
                    Department’s letter of the 26th instant, relative to the Japanese battleship <hi
                        rend="italic">Hizen</hi>, I have the honor to communicate further cablegrams
                    from the collector of customs at Honolulu, as follows:</p>
                <p>Honolulu, October 26, 1914, 5:45 p.m. Captain Brown of the revenue cutter <hi
                        rend="italic">Thetis</hi> reports that steam launches from the Japanese
                    battleship <hi rend="italic">Hizen</hi> were again in neutral waters last night
                    without lights.</p>
                <p>Honolulu, October 26, 1914, 12:45 p.m. Captain <hi rend="italic">Hisen</hi>
                    desires to send sealed communications to the Japanese consul and receive sealed
                    replies. Await instructions.</p>
                <p>By direction of the Secretary,</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NBR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">B. R. Newton</hi>
                        </persName>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
